title: Friendly Zoo — Room-Occupant Slot (ADR-195 S1)
story: friendly-zoo
description: The {slot:here} room-occupant channel — 0/1/N presence clauses staged by independent occupants and joined under one punctuation authority at realize time.

# ADR-195 S1: each occupant present in the player's room appends a bare presence
# clause to the room description's {slot:here} (sentence mode). Zero contributions
# leave the stem + terminator clean; one and many join after the description's
# terminator as independent sentences. Occupant order is fixed (AC-5).
---

# --- 0 occupants: the Zoo Entrance has no presence entities; the slot is clean ---
> look
[OK: contains "Zoo Entrance"]
[OK: contains "wrought-iron gates"]
[OK: not contains "Sam the zookeeper is here"]
[OK: not contains "mill about"]
[OK: not contains "scarlet macaw watches you"]

# --- 1 occupant (NPC): the zookeeper is on the Main Path at the start of play ---
> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]
[OK: contains "Sam the zookeeper is here, jingling a ring of keys."]

# --- N occupants: the Petting Zoo holds both the goats AND the rabbits ---
> east
[OK: contains "Petting Zoo"]
[OK: contains "Three pygmy goats mill about hopefully"]
[OK: contains "Holland Lop rabbits lounges near the hay bale"]

# --- head back west toward the Aviary ---
> west
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

# --- 1 occupant: the scarlet macaw is fixed in the Aviary ---
> west
[OK: contains "Aviary"]
[OK: contains "A scarlet macaw watches you with one bright, knowing eye."]
